Example masterlist

Source: vignettes/example-masterlist.Rmd
example-masterlist.Rmd

The Census APIs have over 200 endpoints, covering dozens of different datasets.

library(censusapi)

To see a current table of every available endpoint, run listCensusApis:

apis <- listCensusApis()
View(apis)

Example master list

Here is a work in progress list of examples for each API. More to come.

American Community Survey

acs_income <- getCensus(name = "acs/acs5",
    vintage = 2016, 
    vars = c("NAME", "B19013_001E", "B19013_001EA", "B19013_001M", "B19013_001MA"), 
    region = "tract:*",
    regionin = "state:02")
head(acs_income)
#>   state county  tract                                               NAME
#> 1    02    013 000100     Census Tract 1, Aleutians East Borough, Alaska
#> 2    02    016 000100 Census Tract 1, Aleutians West Census Area, Alaska

#> 5    02    020 000102  Census Tract 1.02, Anchorage Municipality, Alaska
#> 6    02    020 000201  Census Tract 2.01, Anchorage Municipality, Alaska

American Community Survey Migration Flows 

flows <- getCensus(name = "acs/flows",
    vintage = "2015",
    vars = c("MOVEDIN", "FULL2_NAME", "FULL1_NAME"),
    region = "county:*",
    regionin = "state:6")
head(flows)
#>   state county MOVEDIN        FULL2_NAME                 FULL1_NAME
#> 1    06    001     861            Africa Alameda County, California
#> 2    06    001   11072              Asia Alameda County, California
#> 3    06    001    1733   Central America Alameda County, California
#> 4    06    001      18         Caribbean Alameda County, California
#> 5    06    001    2802            Europe Alameda County, California
#> 6    06    001      55 U.S. Island Areas Alameda County, California

Annual Survey of Manufactures 

asm_state <- getCensus(name = "timeseries/asm/state",
    vars = c("NAICS_TTL", "EMP", "GEO_TTL"),
    region = "state:*",
    time = "2016",
    naics = "31-33")
head(asm_state)
#>   time state     NAICS_TTL     EMP    GEO_TTL NAICS
#> 1 2016    01 Manufacturing  234803    Alabama 31-33
#> 2 2016    02 Manufacturing   12178     Alaska 31-33
#> 3 2016    04 Manufacturing  136946    Arizona 31-33
#> 4 2016    05 Manufacturing  145733   Arkansas 31-33
#> 5 2016    06 Manufacturing 1119896 California 31-33
#> 6 2016    08 Manufacturing  121069   Colorado 31-33
asm_product <- getCensus(name = "timeseries/asm/product",
    vars = c("PSCODE_TTL", "GEO_TTL", "PRODVAL"),
    region = "us:*",
    time = "2016",
    pscode = "311111")
head(asm_product)
#>   time us                     PSCODE_TTL       GEO_TTL  PRODVAL PSCODE
#> 1 2016  1 Dog and cat food manufacturing United States 22933334 311111

Decennial Census

    vars = "P0010001", 
    region = "block:*", regionin = "state:36+county:027")

Economic Indicators 

eits <- getCensus(name = "timeseries/eits/resconst",
    vars = c("cell_value", "data_type_code", "time_slot_id", "error_data", "category_code", "seasonally_adj"),
    region = "us:*",
    time = "from 2004-05 to 2012-12")
head(eits)
#>   cell_value data_type_code time_slot_id error_data category_code
#> 1        677          TOTAL          756         no  ACOMPLETIONS

Population Estimates and Projections 

popest <- getCensus(name = "pep/population",
    vintage = "2016",
    vars = c("POP", "GEONAME", "DATE_DESC"),
    region = "state:*",
    date = "9")
head(popest)
#>   state      POP    GEONAME                        DATE_DESC DATE
